    "Consider the coupling matching x i,j to x i,j + ∆x i,j for each i, we bound the transport cost as below:W 2 2 (ρ j, ν j) ≤ 1 N N i=1 (∆x i,j) 2 = α 2 β ⊤ j Σβ j,which leads to the claimed inequality.",
    "E.3 Proof of Theorem 2Lemma 1 (Gaussian tail bound).",
    "Let Φ(u) denote the standard normal CDF and Q(u):= 1 -Φ(u).",
    "For any u > 0,Q(u) ≤ 1 2 e -u 2 /2.Proof of Lemma 1.",
    "We discuss the bound under two cases.Case 1: When u > 2 π, through integration by parts, we haveQ(u) = 1 √ 2π ∞ u e -t 2 /2 dt ≤ 1 √ 2π e -u 2 /2 u - ∞ u e -t 2 /2 t 2 dt.Dropping the negative integral preserves the inequality, yieldingQ(u) ≤ 1 u √ 2π e -u 2 /2 ≤ 1 2 e u 2 /2.Case 2: When 0 < u ≤ 2 π, we haved du 1 2 e -u 2 /2 = - u 2 e -u 2 /2 ≥ - 1 √ 2π e -u 2 /2 = d du Q(u),where the inequality follows from u ≤ 2 π."
